**Put-Call Parity and Arbitrage.** European call: $S=\$100$, $K=\$105$, $r=5\%$/year, $T=1$ yr, $C=\$8$. \begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph{*})]\item State Put-Call Parity.

\item Find the fair put price.

\item If the put is priced at \$10, construct an explicit arbitrage portfolio.\end{enumerate}

**One-Step Binomial Tree.** Stock at \$50; up to \$65 or down to \$40 in 1 year; $r=5\%$. \begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph{*})]\item Find risk-neutral probabilities $p^{*}$, $1-p^{*}$.

\item Price a European call with $K=\$55$.

\item Verify via replicating portfolio.\end{enumerate}

**Volatility Smile and Market Reality.** \begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph{*})]\item What is the volatility smile/smirk?

\item Why do equity index puts have higher implied vol?

\item Name two model extensions that capture the smile.\end{enumerate}
